      <div class="container"> <h1 id="Car-Brand-Head">Acura SLX</h1> <table class="car-overview"> <tr class="car-overview"> <th class="car-overview-head">Overview</th> <td class="car-overview"> <p class="car-overview-text"><strong>Name:</strong> Acura SLX</p> <p class="car-overview-text"><strong>Generation:</strong> 1st (1997-2002)</p> <p class="car-overview-text"><strong>Platform:</strong> Isuzu Trooper</p> </td> </tr> <tr class="car-overview"> <th class="car-overview-head">Design and Features</th> <td class="car-overview"> <p class="car-overview-text"><strong>Design:</strong> 6-door body style with 4 conventional passenger doors and a 70/30 two-sided rear door</p> <p class="car-overview-text"><strong>Engine:</strong> 3.2-liter, single-overhead-camshaft V-6 engine with 4 valves per cylinder, producing 190 horsepower</p> <p class="car-overview-text"><strong>Transmission:</strong> 4-speed automatic with "power mode" and "winter mode"</p> <p class="car-overview-text"><strong>Drivetrain:</strong> Shift-on-the-fly 4-wheel-drive system</p> <p class="car-overview-text"><strong>Suspension:</strong> Double-wishbone front suspension and multi-link rear suspension</p> <p class="car-overview-text"><strong>Brakes:</strong> Ventilated disc brakes all around with 4-wheel Anti-Lock Braking System (ABS)</p> <p class="car-overview-text"><strong>Frame:</strong> Steel frame with box-section members for added strength and rigidity</p> <p class="car-overview-text"><strong>Safety:</strong> Dual SRS air bags</p> <p class="car-overview-text"><strong>Optional Premium Package:</strong> Leather seating surfaces, power-adjustable front seats, heated front seats, limited-slip rear differential, machine-finish aluminum wheels</p> </td> </tr> <tr class="car-overview"> <th class="car-overview-head">Concepts and Goals</th> <td class="car-overview"> <p class="car-overview-text"><strong>Concept:</strong> Provide a luxury SUV with a remarkable level of comfort, luxury amenities, and off-road capability</p> <p class="car-overview-text"><strong>Goals:</strong> Offer a smooth, quiet ride and exceptional highway handling response with the full complement of amenities and safety features expected in a luxury sedan, while also providing excellent off-road performance</p> </td> </tr> <tr class="car-overview"> <th class="car-overview-head">Competitive Landscape</th> <td class="car-overview"> <p class="car-overview-text">The Acura SLX was designed to compete with the Land Rover Range Rover and Discovery, Lexus LX450, Toyota Land Cruiser, Nissan Pathfinder, and higher trim levels of domestic SUVs such as the Ford Explorer, Jeep Grand Cherokee, and Chevy/GMC Blazer.</p> </td> </tr> <tr class="car-overview"> <th class="car-overview-head">Pricing and Availability</th> <td class="car-overview"> <p class="car-overview-text"><strong>Pricing:</strong> The Acura SLX was priced similarly to its competitors, around $30,000.</p> <p class="car-overview-text"><strong>Availability:</strong> The Acura SLX was manufactured in Japan and sold in the United States through Acura dealerships.</p> </td> </tr> <tr class="car-overview"> <th class="car-overview-head">Controversy</th> <td class="car-overview"> <p class="car-overview-text">In 1996, Consumer Reports tested the Acura SLX and Isuzu Trooper (on which the SLX was based) and found they could roll over during sudden turns at low speeds. Consumer Reports demanded a recall of the vehicles, but Acura and Isuzu defended the safety of their SUVs when driven responsibly.</p> </td> </tr> <tr class="car-overview"> <th class="car-overview-head">Conclusion</th> <td class="car-overview"> <p class="car-overview-text"><strong>Summary:</strong> The Acura SLX was designed to provide a luxury SUV experience with a remarkable level of comfort, luxury amenities, and off-road capability, while also offering a smooth, quiet ride and exceptional highway handling response.</p> <p class="car-overview-text"><strong>Target Market:</strong> The Acura SLX was targeted at affluent buyers who were looking for an upmarket SUV that could provide the same level of luxury and amenities as a premium sedan, while also offering the utility and off-road performance of a traditional SUV.</p> </td> </tr> </table> </div>
